Blockchain Roles – Wipro, Infosys, Accenture 

1. Wipro – Blockchain Roles (Current & Past)

1.1 Senior Blockchain Developer (Closed)
Organization: Wipro
Experience: 5+ years software development, 3+ years blockchain
Role Summary:
Design, develop, and optimize blockchain applications with a focus on stablecoin/token issuance, crypto trading platforms, and multi-chain interoperability.
Key Responsibilities:
Develop smart contracts for token lifecycle management, DEX/CEX trading logic, and AMM pools.
Integrate with multiple blockchain networks (Ethereum/EVM chains, Layer 2s, Cosmos, Solana).
Implement secure coding standards, testing frameworks, and oracle integrations.
Collaborate with security, DevOps, and compliance teams.
Skills Required:
Solidity and Rust programming.
Frameworks: Hardhat, Foundry, Anchor.
Token standards: ERC-20, ERC-4626.
Strong understanding of DEX/AMM mechanics, oracles, and compliance workflows.

1.2 Blockchain Consultant (Open)
Organization: Wipro
Experience: 6+ years in blockchain consulting/architecture
Role Summary:
Provide strategic blockchain consultancy, solution architecture, and oversight for enterprise blockchain projects including tokenization and trading systems.
Key Responsibilities:
Advise clients on blockchain strategy and architecture.
Design enterprise blockchain solutions using EVM chains, Layer 2s, Cosmos, and interoperability protocols.
Translate business requirements into scalable technical solutions.
Skills Required:
Strong experience in stablecoin design and crypto trading platforms.
Deep understanding of blockchain security, custody, and regulatory compliance.

1.3 Blockchain Architect (Open)
Organization: Wipro
Role Summary:
Lead the architecture of blockchain platforms including stablecoin/token infrastructure, interoperability, wallets, custody, and compliance integrations.
Key Responsibilities:
Architect core platform components such as mint/burn mechanisms, treasury systems, and oracle workflows.
Select appropriate blockchains, Layer 2s, and cross-chain solutions.
Integrate secure wallets, custody platforms, analytics, and compliance systems.
Skills Required:
Hands-on experience with Solidity and Rust.
Cloud platforms: AWS, Azure, or GCP.
Knowledge of token standards, threat modeling, audit processes, MEV, rollups, and cross-chain protocols.

Past / Archived Roles at Wipro
Blockchain Developer roles focusing on EVM, cryptography, blockchain fundamentals, and system integration.
Note: These indicate Wipro’s continued interest in blockchain talent and may reopen in the future.


2. Infosys – Blockchain Roles (Current & Past)
2.1 Blockchain Developer (Open)
Organization: Infosys
Role Summary:
Develop enterprise blockchain solutions using platforms such as Hyperledger Fabric, R3 Corda, and Ethereum, with focus on on-chain/off-chain data optimization.
Key Responsibilities:
Implement blockchain backends and smart contract interfaces.
Design efficient on-chain and off-chain data architectures.
Collaborate with Agile teams across the full SDLC lifecycle.
Skills Required:
Strong understanding of DLT fundamentals and consensus algorithms.
Java/J2EE, Spring Boot, Docker, Jenkins.
Cloud exposure (Azure preferred).
Strong communication and problem-solving skills.

2.2 Blockchain Senior Tech Lead / Architect (Open)
Organization: Infosys
Role Summary:
Lead blockchain architecture initiatives and mentor teams in delivering enterprise-grade blockchain solutions.
Key Responsibilities:
Drive architecture design and solution delivery.
Measure performance and educate teams on blockchain frameworks.
Apply Agile and SDLC best practices.
Skills Required:
Blockchain fundamentals and smart contract development.
Performance benchmarking and architecture design experience.
Tools: Docker, Angular, GoLang, JavaScript.
Strong leadership and communication skills.

Past / Closed Roles at Infosys
Blockchain Senior Developer – Hyperledger, Corda, Ethereum.
Blockchain Architect – DLT frameworks, consensus, and enterprise fundamentals.
Past listings closely mirror current requirements and may reappear.

3. Accenture – Blockchain & Related Technology Roles
3.1 Full Stack Engineer (Blockchain Exposure)
Organization: Accenture
Role Summary:
Develop full-stack enterprise solutions where blockchain is a core enabling technology.
Key Responsibilities:
Build end-to-end applications (frontend and backend).
Integrate blockchain technology into enterprise systems.
Work in cross-functional Agile teams with cloud focus.
Skills Required:
3+ years experience including blockchain exposure.
React.js, Node.js (preferred).
Cloud and DevOps knowledge (Azure).

Other Accenture Roles with Blockchain Relevance
Technology Strategy & Advisory roles.
Product Management and Consulting positions requiring blockchain/DLT understanding.




Common Skills in Demand Across Wipro, Infosys, and Accenture
Blockchain & Distributed Ledger Technologies
Blockchain fundamentals (DLT, consensus mechanisms, cryptography)
Smart contract development and token standards (ERC-20, ERC-721)
Ethereum and EVM-compatible blockchain networks
On-chain and off-chain system integration
Programming & Application Development
Solidity and Rust
Java, JavaScript, TypeScript
Node.js–based backend development
Frameworks, Tools & Platforms
Smart contract frameworks: Hardhat, Foundry
Enterprise blockchain platforms: Hyperledger Fabric, R3 Corda
Application frameworks: Spring Boot
Containerization and DevOps tools: Docker, CI/CD pipelines
Cloud & Infrastructure
Cloud platforms: AWS, Microsoft Azure, Google Cloud Platform (GCP)
Security & Compliance
Secure coding practices for smart contracts
Blockchain security, audit awareness, and compliance fundamentals
Delivery, Collaboration & Methodologies
Agile and SDLC-based project delivery
Effective communication and cross-functional teamwork
Analytical thinking and problem-solving skills

